gomodel:SYNGO_5100  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 7: confocal imaging of dendritic spines in cultured hippocampal neurons (11DIV) expressing controls, wildtype CPEB3 and various CPEB3 mutants showed that CPEB3 overexpression strongly decreased spine density but not in CPEB3-Δubiquitination.\n\n\"However, expressing CPEB3-UbKO resulted in pronounced increase of number of spines and filopodia, whereas CPEB3 fused to either DsRed or SUMO resulted in a phenotype similar to wild type CPEB3. Taken together, our data suggest that the ability of Neurl1 to ubiquitinate CPEB3 is a limiting factor and facilitates hippocampal synaptic plasticity and hippocampal-dependent memory by modulating CPEB3 translational activity through ubiquitination with consequent induction of an increase of GluA1 and GluA2 protein levels and the formation of new spines.\". Experimental description: suppl. M&M:\n\"Hippocampal Cultures - Hippocampi were dissected from C57BL6/J mice at postnatal day 1-2, ...\"\n\nLentivirus Infections of Cultured Hippocampal Neurons\n\"The coding regions of CPEB3, Neurl1-F, Neurl1-F Rm , CPEB3-Ub KO , CPEB3-EGFP, CPEB3- SUMO and CPEB3ΔNter were amplified by PCR from their original vectors and subcloned into the FUGW vector (kind gift of Pavel Osten, Dittgen et al., 2004; 5'linker: AgeI or BamHI; 3'linker: EcoRI or BsrGI). For the production of lentiviruses, the FUGW constructs were co-transfected with the two helper plasmids pMD2.G and psPax2 plasmids (Addgene) in HEK293FT cells (Invitrogen) following the manufacturer's instructions.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5100" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

